OL,6,FAsked why the situation has become so
OL,7,Fbad, she said: "London is like the
OL,8,Fepicentre of the housing crisis.
OL,10,F"56% of all homeless people nationally
OL,11,Flive in London...the reason
OL,12,Fhomelessness is so bad is a really bad
OL,13,Fcombination of things like massive
OL,14,Freductions in the number of landlords
OL,15,Fthat are in London, the fact that
OL,16,Fhousing costs are so high and the lack
OL,17,Fof home building over a long period..."
OL,19,FCllr Williams told ITV News of the
OL,20,Fimplications of this in her borough.
